## How to Use This Rule

**This rule applies automatically to all code changes and development work.**

**Agents should:**
- Run light lint pass as part of `pre-flight-check` before coding
- Fix lint issues in files you touch while coding
- Run full lint pass before PR submission with `pr-review-check`
- Use auto-fix capabilities when available (ESLint --fix, Prettier, Ruff, Black)
- Respect existing linter configs (don't change without explicit task)
- Report lint status once per major change (don't repeatedly promise fixes)

*This rule guides AI agent behavior around linting. For detailed requirements and policies, see `standards/process/code-quality-linting-standards.md`.*
